WEBVTT

00:03.203 --> 00:14.479
♪♪

00:14.481 --> 00:16.881
[ Sniffs ]

00:16.883 --> 00:20.185
♪♪

00:21.221 --> 00:22.487
Whatcha doing?

00:22.489 --> 00:23.888
Just putting up
some more flyers.

00:23.890 --> 00:25.758
The ones I put up
the other day disappeared.

00:25.760 --> 00:27.960
So, you gonna hang around
for a while, or...?

00:27.962 --> 00:32.665
I would, but I got to put up
all these flyers around town.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.368
Hey, could somebody
shut the door?

00:36.370 --> 00:38.703
I think we got a draft
in here.

00:38.705 --> 00:40.372
[ Chuckles ]

00:40.374 --> 00:41.774
Hi.

00:41.776 --> 00:43.575
I'm here to pick up the key
to Bare Feet Retreat.

00:43.577 --> 00:45.844
I don't know
if you remember me, but --

00:45.846 --> 00:47.312
Oh, I remember you.

00:47.314 --> 00:48.781
Shit.
Boy, do I remember you.

00:48.783 --> 00:50.649
Yeah, last time
you rented the house,

00:50.651 --> 00:52.717
I had to re-hang
all the pictures.

00:52.719 --> 00:54.453
I'm still getting sand
out of the knickknacks,

00:54.455 --> 00:56.388
and half the spoons
were gone.

00:56.390 --> 00:58.590
It's not easy finding
matching spoons, okay?

00:58.592 --> 01:00.325
And in fact,
they won't truly match

01:00.327 --> 01:03.728
until the new ones lose their
shine and muster up a patina.

01:03.730 --> 01:05.597
No parties this time,
I hope.

01:08.402 --> 01:10.903
No parties. I promise.

01:14.274 --> 01:16.508
All right, well,
I'll see you later.

01:19.880 --> 01:21.946
There was a-a bug.

01:21.948 --> 01:25.684
♪♪

01:25.686 --> 01:28.620
Tim:<i> I want to assure you that</i>
<i> I won't be having any parties,</i>

01:28.622 --> 01:31.156
<i> but I do owe you an explanation</i>
<i> about something.</i>

01:31.158 --> 01:33.425
<i> It's a long story,</i>
<i> and it all started last year</i>

01:33.427 --> 01:34.559
<i> on my birthday.</i>

01:34.561 --> 01:37.295
Hey, there's my Walt.

01:37.297 --> 01:39.698
Tell me those
are my new shoes.

01:39.700 --> 01:50.375
♪♪

01:50.377 --> 01:51.710
Hi.

01:51.712 --> 01:53.645
Uh, we're here to pick up
the keys to Bare Feet Retreat.

01:53.647 --> 01:56.381
Oh, yeah. Uh, you're gonna have
to look for my boyfriend.

01:56.383 --> 01:59.184
He's --

01:59.186 --> 02:00.252
You're diarrhea.

02:00.254 --> 02:01.520
Ha! See?

02:01.522 --> 02:03.655
I told you that commercial
would get you chicks.

02:03.657 --> 02:05.990
We're both actors. I mainly do
corporate training videos,

02:05.992 --> 02:07.792
but if you worked
for Kaiser Permanente,

02:07.794 --> 02:09.662
you would be losing
your shit right now.

02:09.664 --> 02:12.531
She doesn't care about --
She does.

02:12.533 --> 02:13.798
We just need the keys.

02:13.800 --> 02:15.600
Okay, well, um, he's just
in the back,

02:15.602 --> 02:17.269
cleaning spaghetti
off the marlin.

02:17.271 --> 02:19.204
[ Chuckles ] We had a 2-year-old
in here earlier

02:19.206 --> 02:21.407
that was acting
like a real prick.

02:23.544 --> 02:24.877
I'm here
about the beach house.

02:24.879 --> 02:26.344
Yeah, can you
give me a sec?

02:26.346 --> 02:29.281
I just have to get these noodles
off before they crust up.

02:29.283 --> 02:32.217
[ Cellphone rings, beeps ]

02:32.219 --> 02:33.351
Hello?

02:33.353 --> 02:34.352
Uh, sorry to bother you,
Mr. Davis,

02:34.354 --> 02:36.688
but I have a DJ Maureen here

02:36.690 --> 02:39.758
looking to set up
some party or whatnot.

02:39.760 --> 02:42.827
And between you and me,
she's got a half a tattoo,

02:42.829 --> 02:44.697
and I wouldn't mind
seeing the other half.

02:44.699 --> 02:45.898
Shit.

02:45.900 --> 02:48.100
Look, I told her the party
was at the beach.

02:48.102 --> 02:51.303
The address is 246 Sandyland Way
in Mabel Beach.

02:51.305 --> 02:54.639
And it's a surprise, so tell her
not to show up until 9:00.

02:54.641 --> 02:55.640
[ Cellphone beeps ]

02:55.642 --> 02:56.841
You guys
having a party?

02:56.843 --> 02:58.310
Uh, just a little one.

02:58.312 --> 03:00.713
Is -- is that a problem?
Not for me,

03:00.715 --> 03:03.115
but you probably don't want
my boyfriend to find out.

03:03.117 --> 03:04.182
It's his mom's house.

03:04.184 --> 03:05.850
Uh, you know, you can come
if you want, actually.

03:05.852 --> 03:07.652
It's -- It's diarrhea's
birthday.

03:07.654 --> 03:09.654
Oh, I don't know.

03:09.656 --> 03:11.423
I'd have to sneak out.

03:12.993 --> 03:16.595
But I did just get
these new shoes.

03:16.597 --> 03:17.930
No, you know what?

03:17.932 --> 03:20.065
It's Friday, and Tommy
was looking forward

03:20.067 --> 03:22.066
to pot roast pajama night.

03:22.068 --> 03:23.268
[ Sighs ]

03:23.270 --> 03:24.869
Are you sure?

03:24.871 --> 03:27.406
Those shoes look like they
deserve to stay up past 8:30.

03:27.408 --> 03:29.541
[ Laughing ] 8:30?

03:29.543 --> 03:30.875
We're not that lame.

03:30.877 --> 03:33.345
We don't go to bed till
after "Blue Bloods."

03:33.347 --> 03:35.280
So, I don't know what you guys
have up your sleeve

03:35.282 --> 03:36.615
as far as activities,

03:36.617 --> 03:38.082
but there's a whole shelf
full of games.

03:38.084 --> 03:40.352
For two players,
may I recommend Farkle?

03:40.354 --> 03:42.220
It's like Yahtzee
on steroids.

03:42.222 --> 03:45.290
Thanks. See you later.

03:45.292 --> 03:47.292
You know, I was thinking
about spicing things up tonight,

03:47.294 --> 03:49.694
throwing a square of dark
chocolate into the pot roast.

03:49.696 --> 03:51.896
Think I saw it
on "The Chew."

03:51.898 --> 03:53.231
Oh.

03:53.233 --> 03:57.936
♪♪

03:59.573 --> 04:01.440
This actually looks
kind of fun.

04:01.442 --> 04:05.510
Maybe after we order dinner,
we can --

04:05.512 --> 04:06.711
Eat this birthday cookie.

04:06.713 --> 04:08.981
What kind of coo--
Nom, nom, nom.

04:08.983 --> 04:10.315
There's weed in this,
isn't there?

04:10.317 --> 04:11.316
Quite a bit.

04:11.318 --> 04:13.318
Thanks. I think.

04:13.320 --> 04:15.654
You know I haven't gotten high
since the breakup?

04:15.656 --> 04:16.921
It reminds me
of Jennifer --

04:16.923 --> 04:18.190
Yeah, I know, all right?

04:18.192 --> 04:20.058
But you can't not ever
get high again

04:20.060 --> 04:22.527
just because drugs remind you
of your ex-girlfriend.

04:22.529 --> 04:23.728
It's not healthy, man.

04:23.730 --> 04:25.664
[ Knock on door ]

04:25.666 --> 04:27.599
Who's that?

04:27.601 --> 04:30.535
I think it's my Uncle Bill.

04:30.537 --> 04:32.838
Looks like the old man
from "Up."

04:36.377 --> 04:37.909
<i> In order for you to understand</i>

04:37.911 --> 04:39.644
<i> why seeing my Uncle Bill</i>
<i> outside your beach house</i>

04:39.646 --> 04:41.246
<i> was so strange,</i>

04:41.248 --> 04:42.581
<i> you need to know</i>
<i> a few things about him.</i>

04:42.583 --> 04:45.116
<i> Bill grew up in West Virginia,</i>
<i> and at 15,</i>

04:45.118 --> 04:48.187
<i> he started working</i>
<i> in the coal mines with his dad.</i>

04:48.189 --> 04:51.056
<i> He met his wife, Lorraine,</i>
<i> when he was 22.</i>

04:51.058 --> 04:53.592
<i> They couldn't have children,</i>
<i> so for the next 50 years,</i>

04:53.594 --> 04:55.594
<i> they spent their time</i>
<i> going to church,</i>

04:55.596 --> 04:57.863
<i> laying in the backyard</i>
<i> looking at clouds,</i>

04:57.865 --> 05:02.201
<i> playing cards with friends,</i>
<i> and just being in love.</i>

05:02.203 --> 05:04.603
<i> It was a simple life.</i>

05:04.605 --> 05:07.338
♪♪

05:07.340 --> 05:08.940
<i> A few years ago, I got the news</i>

05:08.942 --> 05:11.276
<i> that Lorraine died</i>
<i> of a heart attack.</i>

05:11.278 --> 05:14.079
<i> If my parents were still alive,</i>
<i> I might've gone to the funeral,</i>

05:14.081 --> 05:17.416
<i> but without somebody pressuring</i>
<i> me to go, I didn't.</i>

05:17.418 --> 05:19.684
<i> It was selfish,</i>
<i> especially because</i>

05:19.686 --> 05:22.353
<i> even though I hadn't seen Bill</i>
<i> since I was 5,</i>

05:22.355 --> 05:27.759
<i> he never forgot my birthday.</i>

05:27.761 --> 05:29.028
Happy birthday.

05:29.030 --> 05:30.962
Thanks.

05:30.964 --> 05:32.163
What are you doing here?

05:32.165 --> 05:33.432
Well, I went
to your apartment,

05:33.434 --> 05:37.302
and the man in charge
of the lobby said you was here.

05:37.304 --> 05:39.704
Hi. I'm Bill.

05:39.706 --> 05:40.839
Joe.

05:40.841 --> 05:43.642
I reckoned this year I'd deliver
your card by hand.

05:43.644 --> 05:45.644
Could I use your washroom?

05:45.646 --> 05:47.312
I tried to use the one
on the bus,

05:47.314 --> 05:50.916
but I couldn't hold my breath
that long.

05:50.918 --> 05:54.786
[ Clears throat ]

05:54.788 --> 05:59.391
[ Sighs ]

05:59.393 --> 06:01.860
Well, you better hurry up.
Pop into your PJs.

06:01.862 --> 06:04.063
Yeah, actually,
my sister just texted.

06:04.065 --> 06:05.597
I have to babysit now.

06:05.599 --> 06:06.932
That's a little last-minute.

06:06.934 --> 06:09.334
Yeah, she matched
with someone on Tinder.

06:09.336 --> 06:11.270
Okay.
Well, um,

06:11.272 --> 06:13.405
I could put the roast back
in the pot, let it simmer,

06:13.407 --> 06:15.140
keep my hunger at bay
with a handful of raisins.

06:15.142 --> 06:16.541
No, you know,
it's fine.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.343
Um, she sounds like
she's in a slutty mood,

06:18.345 --> 06:20.545
so I could be stuck there
all night.

06:20.547 --> 06:22.481
Well, I guess I could tape
"Blue Bloods."

06:22.483 --> 06:24.415
Although
it's a new one tonight,

06:24.417 --> 06:25.817
and I got a Shriners meeting
in the morning.

06:25.819 --> 06:28.887
There's no way Glen doesn't
let a spoiler slip out.

06:28.889 --> 06:30.889
Maybe I could watch it

06:30.891 --> 06:33.959
and then you and I could
watch it together later?

06:33.961 --> 06:35.294
Sounds great.
[ Chuckles ]

06:35.296 --> 06:36.761
You seem to enjoy watching
the repeats

06:36.763 --> 06:38.097
more than
the originals anyways.

06:38.099 --> 06:40.365
Yeah, well, I'm a lot less
stressed the second go-around,

06:40.367 --> 06:42.701
that's for sure.

06:42.703 --> 06:43.969
You got to
get rid of him.

06:43.971 --> 06:45.236
I'm throwing you a party.

06:45.238 --> 06:46.305
DJ Maureen is coming.

06:46.307 --> 06:47.706
Seriously?

06:47.708 --> 06:50.909
We haven't hung out with her
since the last time we took...

06:50.911 --> 06:52.311
That's a lot of ecstasy.

06:52.313 --> 06:55.447
[ Coughing ]

06:55.449 --> 06:57.182
You know,
I was thinking, uh,

06:57.184 --> 06:59.918
maybe us two could
go fishing again.

06:59.920 --> 07:02.587
You remember the last time
we went fishing?

07:02.589 --> 07:05.324
You couldn't have been
more than 5.

07:05.326 --> 07:08.259
A big, old catfish got ahold
of your line

07:08.261 --> 07:10.929
and yanked you
right out of the boat.

07:10.931 --> 07:13.598
Yeah, I started crying,
and if I remember correctly,

07:13.600 --> 07:14.866
you started laughing.

07:14.868 --> 07:16.535
[ Chuckles ] I had to.

07:16.537 --> 07:18.203
Oh, you was terrified.

07:18.205 --> 07:22.141
I needed to let you know that
everything's gonna be okay,

07:22.143 --> 07:23.542
and it worked.

07:23.544 --> 07:24.943
You caught
the sillies from me,

07:24.945 --> 07:28.013
and then you started
laughing yourself.

07:28.015 --> 07:30.949
That's true. I did.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.751
[ Ecstasy rattles ]

07:32.753 --> 07:34.019
You must be tired.

07:34.021 --> 07:35.754
How about I help you
find a hotel nearby?

07:35.756 --> 07:37.622
I'm dying.

07:37.624 --> 07:40.625
[ Crickets chirping ]

07:40.627 --> 07:43.362
-Okay.
-I've got pneumoconiosis.

07:43.364 --> 07:46.297
It's commonly known
as Black Lung.

07:46.299 --> 07:47.766
My lungs are black.

07:50.103 --> 07:51.436
[ Knock on door ]

07:51.438 --> 07:54.105
Police! We're here to take
all your drugs!

07:54.107 --> 07:55.841
[ Laughs ]

07:55.843 --> 07:58.844
Happy birthday!
[ Cheering ]

07:58.846 --> 08:02.514
Oh, shit, you brought
the doorman, you crazy bitch.

08:02.516 --> 08:05.184
[ Indistinct chatter ]

08:05.186 --> 08:07.052
You'uns fixing
to have a party?

08:07.054 --> 08:10.189
Yeah, but it's not the kind
of party you would...

08:10.191 --> 08:12.992
My friend, he, uh...

08:12.994 --> 08:16.661
I don't do drugs, but some of
the people who are coming, uh --

08:16.663 --> 08:18.663
If there's gonna
be drugs at your party,

08:18.665 --> 08:20.199
I'd like to stay.

08:20.201 --> 08:21.666
Excuse me?

08:21.668 --> 08:23.402
I would be willing to try
some of them drugs.

08:23.404 --> 08:25.204
I don't --
What?

08:25.206 --> 08:29.208
Tim, I lived the way I thought
I was supposed to for 90 years,

08:29.210 --> 08:32.277
and there were a whole lot of
rewards along the way

08:32.279 --> 08:34.013
for doing so.

08:34.015 --> 08:36.081
Met a great woman.

08:36.083 --> 08:39.484
And since I was
faithful to her,

08:39.486 --> 08:41.486
she never left my side.

08:41.488 --> 08:44.089
I ain't never
touched alcohol.

08:44.091 --> 08:45.424
And because of that,

08:45.426 --> 08:48.427
I ain't never done nothing
that I've regretted.

08:48.429 --> 08:50.429
But lately,
I've been asking myself

08:50.431 --> 08:54.032
if I lived
too safe a life.

08:54.034 --> 08:57.302
What I'm saying is that I want
to see what life is like

08:57.304 --> 08:59.771
when I don't play
by the rules.

08:59.773 --> 09:02.173
My only fear is that,
if I like it,

09:02.175 --> 09:07.378
I'm gonna kick myself for
waiting 90 years to start.

09:07.380 --> 09:09.180
[ Cheering ]

09:09.182 --> 09:10.315
All right, everybody.

09:10.317 --> 09:12.383
Here we go.

09:12.385 --> 09:14.319
On you mark...

09:14.321 --> 09:16.054
get set...

09:16.056 --> 09:16.855
go!

09:16.857 --> 09:19.524
♪♪

09:19.526 --> 09:22.994
[ Cheering ]

09:22.996 --> 09:24.263
I don't feel nothing yet.

09:24.265 --> 09:27.399
Yeah, it's gonna take
about 45 minutes to kick in.

09:27.401 --> 09:30.068
Okay, but if I fall asleep
before then,

09:30.070 --> 09:32.705
be sure to wake me.

09:35.809 --> 09:38.143
<i> Ecstasy can affect people</i>
<i> in different ways.</i>

09:38.145 --> 09:39.811
<i> Some people get creative</i>

09:39.813 --> 09:42.280
<i> and start to look at the world</i>
<i> in a different way.</i>

09:42.282 --> 09:46.351
♪♪

09:46.353 --> 09:48.353
<i> Some people dance.</i>

09:48.355 --> 09:51.623
♪♪

09:51.625 --> 09:53.959
<i> Some people like to touch</i>
<i> and be touched.</i>

09:53.961 --> 09:59.765
♪♪

09:59.767 --> 10:02.368
<i> Me? I tend to</i>
<i> get introspective.</i>

10:02.370 --> 10:04.636
I'm thinking
about quitting acting.

10:04.638 --> 10:06.772
Why?
You're so famous.

10:06.774 --> 10:09.174
For being the face
of diarrhea.

10:09.176 --> 10:10.642
Ah.

10:10.644 --> 10:12.444
I just don't want to end up
like our doorman.

10:12.446 --> 10:14.913
He used to be an actor,
and the rumor is

10:14.915 --> 10:17.048
that he ended up
doing porn.

10:17.050 --> 10:18.784
No.

10:18.786 --> 10:20.786
[ Inhales deeply ]

10:20.788 --> 10:22.588
I feel real good.

10:22.590 --> 10:24.189
You guys feel real good?

10:24.191 --> 10:25.457
[ Chuckles ] Amazing.

10:25.459 --> 10:26.724
We feel great.

10:26.726 --> 10:28.526
[ Sighs ]

10:28.528 --> 10:30.796
[ Fuzz scratching ]

10:30.798 --> 10:34.132
[ Sighs ] I can't believe
I was gonna eat pot roast

10:34.134 --> 10:37.135
and watch "Blue Bloods"
with my boyfriend tonight.

10:37.137 --> 10:38.937
[ Chuckles ]
Where'd you guys meet?

10:38.939 --> 10:42.874
Mm. We dropped out
of law school together.

10:42.876 --> 10:48.414
He's really, really, really,
really, really, really, really,

10:48.416 --> 10:51.883
really, really, really, really,
really, really, really, really,

10:51.885 --> 10:55.220
really nice.

10:55.222 --> 10:57.155
He sounds nice.

10:57.157 --> 10:58.824
Yeah.

10:58.826 --> 11:03.095
This is the first time
I've done euphoria.

11:03.097 --> 11:04.229
Me, too.

11:04.231 --> 11:06.765
Remember we talked about that
in the kitchen?

11:06.767 --> 11:08.967
It's called
ecstasy, Bill.

11:08.969 --> 11:10.101
What is?

11:10.103 --> 11:12.037
-Ah.
-The drug. It's called ecstasy.

11:12.039 --> 11:13.171
What did I say?

11:13.173 --> 11:15.307
[ Laughing ] I don't know.
Something else.

11:15.309 --> 11:16.708
[ Laughs ]

11:16.710 --> 11:18.776
[ Sighs ] I just wish Tommy
wouldn't act like

11:18.778 --> 11:21.046
we're already
an old married couple.

11:21.048 --> 11:26.117
Last weekend, we put together a
puzzle I bought at a yard sale.

11:26.119 --> 11:27.719
I like puzzles.

11:27.721 --> 11:28.854
[ Chuckles ] Me, too.

11:28.856 --> 11:31.523
That's why I bought one
at a yard sale.

11:31.525 --> 11:33.725
[ Sighs ]

11:33.727 --> 11:36.594
Your feet are beautiful.

11:36.596 --> 11:39.331
I know. [ Giggles ]

11:39.333 --> 11:41.933
You want to touch them?

11:41.935 --> 11:47.739
It'd be okay?
I think so.

11:47.741 --> 11:49.074
Yeah, it's okay.

11:49.076 --> 11:52.410
Maybe I should be a puzzle maker
instead of an actor.

11:52.412 --> 11:54.480
♪♪

11:54.482 --> 11:55.813
You'd be good at that.

11:55.815 --> 11:59.017
You know what?
I like the corner pieces.

11:59.019 --> 12:01.419
You should make
more corner pieces.

12:01.421 --> 12:03.355
I feel great.

12:03.357 --> 12:05.090
Do you guys feel great?

12:05.092 --> 12:07.893
[ Chuckles ] Amazing.

12:07.895 --> 12:10.762
This is the first time
I've tried euphoria.

12:10.764 --> 12:14.900
<i> The rest of the night</i>
<i> is a bit of a blur,</i>

12:14.902 --> 12:17.435
<i> but I do remember bits</i>
<i> and pieces.</i>

12:17.437 --> 12:21.239
♪♪

12:21.241 --> 12:24.042
<i> Some girl tripped and put her</i>
<i> head through one of your walls,</i>

12:24.044 --> 12:25.511
<i> which she thought</i>
<i> was hysterical.</i>

12:25.513 --> 12:27.379
[ Laughs ]

12:27.381 --> 12:30.315
<i> That led us to finding the</i>
<i> coolest handyman on Craigslist,</i>

12:30.317 --> 12:31.983
<i> who fixed it up like new.</i>

12:31.985 --> 12:34.052
<i> So Joe gave him a nice tip.</i>

12:34.054 --> 12:39.124
♪♪

12:39.126 --> 12:40.658
What was that?

12:40.660 --> 12:44.196
<i> I vaguely remember a robot</i>
<i> that played records.</i>

12:44.198 --> 12:46.798
<i> I also remember my commercial</i>
<i> coming on TV.</i>

12:46.800 --> 12:48.266
